A single plot of land and two of the apartment buildings belong to a private individual, the rest to the municipality of Pliening.
It sells the majority on the open market, 20 plots of land in a socially acceptable model.
According to Frick, the municipality's two apartment buildings are to be built as affordable housing.
With a total of 16 income-oriented apartments subsidised by the Free State.
Space for 200 people
Roughly estimated, living space for about 200 people will be created on the area of the new development area Landsham-Süd.
Not only that: Now, at the beginning of October, according to Frick, the start of the construction of a new daycare center is taking place there.
It will house three kindergarten and three crèche groups as well as a multipurpose room.
The opening is scheduled for September 2019, at the start of the next kindergarten year.
This is how Schalke's Naldo achieves "great sport" on the bench
Not in the starting line-up for the third time in a row: Nevertheless, Naldo thanks Schalke coach Domenico Tedesco.
Gelsenkirchen - After Ronaldo Aparecido Rodrigues had sat for the third time in a row not in the Schalke starting eleven, but on the substitutes' bench, the understanding of many people would have been great if the almost two-meter-tall Brazilian had really talked the frustration from the soul.
But when the Schalke players gathered as usual in the centre circle after the 1-0 victory over FSV Mainz 05 and head coach Domenico Tedesco thanked all his professionals, the 36-year-old, whom everyone calls Naldo for simplicity's sake, intervened and said; "We have to thank you, coach!"
"That was very emotional, that was great sport," Tedesco later said of the reaction of his vice-captain, who had no grudge despite his renewed reservist existence.
Probably, Naldo, who was celebrated as the best Schalke last season, knows that he has actually not been sidelined by his coach - but gets a break for good reasons.
A reason called "load control".
It wasn't easy to tell him
"It wasn't easy to tell him, I'll tell you honestly," Tedesco said of the moment he told Naldo he wasn't in the starting line-up.
He's an important player, he's an important person.
But it's always about the thing, it's about the club," Tedesco explained the step.
Naldo played 90 minutes against Bayern and Porto.
He is 36 years old.
It is important that everyone can catch their breath at the moment.
And that we keep everyone on board," Tedesco explained the rotation, which recently caught Naldo.
And to which the Brazilian reacted with the wisdom of his advanced age: by proving to be an exemplary team player on the bench.
The mood in Austria's industry continued its downward slide in August at an accelerated rate compared to the euro zone.
The purchasing managers' index (PMI) was at a 37-month low of 46.7 points.
Nevertheless, Austria has the third-best mood in Europe behind Ireland and the Netherlands, the Markit Institute said on Monday in response to its survey of 3,000 companies.
Unlike in Austria, the PMI of the euro zone rose by 1.1 points to 45.1 points, but the index is still below the 50-point mark for the 13th month in a row, which indicates growth.
Only Ireland's industry broke this threshold in August with 50.9 points.
Bringing up the rear were the Greeks (42.1 points).
In Germany, France and Spain, the sentiment barometer fell, albeit more slowly than in previous months.
In Spain, the index reached its highest level since March at 44.0 points.
"The slightly weakened downturn could mean that the worst is over," said Markit economist Rob Dobson.
However, industry remains the number one brake on growth - at least in the third quarter.
A rapid return to growth is not in sight: export orders in the eurozone fell more sharply than at any time since November 2011.
As a result, companies cut jobs for the seventh month in a row.
In China, too, industrial production fell more sharply in August than initially assumed.
The sentiment barometer fell from 49.3 points in the previous month to 47.6 points.
Experts had initially expected 47.8 points.
The Purchasing Managers' Index bases its figures on representative surveys of 3,000 European industrial companies.
Among other things, developments in sales, employment, inventories and prices are surveyed.
Tuchel's PSG team achieves eighth win in eighth league game
29. September 2018 at 19:45
Nice coach Thomas Tuchel continues to rush from victory to victory with Paris Saint-Germain in France's football championship.
At OGC Nice, the defending champion won 3-0 (1-0) thanks to two goals from superstar Neymar and was thus also successful in the eighth league game.
The last time Olympique Lyon had made such a good start to the season in France was 82 years ago.
The Brazilian Neymar gave PSG the lead after 22 minutes and made the final score in injury time.
Christopher Nkunku (46th) provided the interim 2:0.
Paris also managed the dress rehearsal for the groundbreaking second Champions League group game against Red Star Belgrade on Wednesday.
At the start of the premier class, Tuchel's team had to accept the only competitive defeat so far this season at 2:3 in Liverpool.
